"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkorion_belt_docs=globalThis.webpackChunkorion_belt_docs||[]).push([[48130],{77735(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"orion-belt-vs-teleport","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/orion-belt-vs-teleport","editUrl":"https://github.com/zrougamed/orion-belt-docs/edit/master/blog/2026-07-16-orion-belt-vs-teleport.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-07-16-orion-belt-vs-teleport.md","title":"Orion Belt vs Teleport (and Boundary / bastions)","description":"Short version: Orion Belt is a self-hosted SSH access gateway with PAM workflows. Teleport is a broad zero-trust access platform. If you mainly need mediated SSH, recording, JIT, and MFA \u2014 without inbound ports on every host or a large ops surface \u2014 Orion Belt is the lighter fit.","date":"2026-07-16T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"SSH","permalink":"/blog/tags/ssh","description":"SSH access, bastions, and tunnels"},{"inline":false,"label":"PAM","permalink":"/blog/tags/pam","description":"Privileged access management"},{"inline":false,"label":"Teleport","permalink":"/blog/tags/teleport","description":"Comparisons and alternatives"},{"inline":false,"label":"Self-hosted","permalink":"/blog/tags/self-hosted","description":"Running infrastructure yourself"}],"readingTime":1.85,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Orion Belt","title":"Maintainers","url":"https://orion-belt.dev","page":{"permalink":"/blog/authors/orion"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/orion-belt-dev"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/orion-belt-dev.png","key":"orion"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"orion-belt-vs-teleport","title":"Orion Belt vs Teleport (and Boundary / bastions)","authors":["orion"],"tags":["ssh","pam","teleport","self-hosted"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Orion Belt v1.0 is out","permalink":"/blog/welcome-orion-belt-v1"}},"content":"**Short version:** Orion Belt is a self-hosted **SSH access gateway with PAM workflows**. Teleport is a **broad zero-trust access platform**. If you mainly need mediated SSH, recording, JIT, and MFA \u2014 without inbound ports on every host or a large ops surface \u2014 Orion Belt is the lighter fit.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n:::info License\\nOrion Belt is Apache 2.0 + Commons Clause (free to self-host/use internally; not for sale as a product/service). Teleport\u2019s licensing is separate \u2014 verify current terms for your use case.\\n:::\\n\\n## Side-by-side\\n\\n| Dimension | Orion Belt | Teleport | Boundary | Traditional bastion |\\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\\n| Primary job | SSH PAM / bastion gateway | Multi-protocol zero-trust | Identity-aware brokering | Network jump point |\\n| Protocols | SSH / SCP (focused) | SSH, K8s, DB, web, \u2026 | Many via workers | Whatever you tunnel |\\n| Target reach | **Agents dial out** | Node agents / tunnels | Workers / proxies | Often inbound |\\n| Session recording | Yes (+ live watch) | Yes | Yes (with path) | DIY |\\n| JIT / approvals | Built-in (+ ChatOps) | Access requests | IdP / workflows | Rare |\\n| Ops weight | Smaller SSH slice | Large platform | Medium\u2013large | Small, feature-poor |\\n| Hosting | Self-hosted | Self-hosted or cloud | Self-hosted or HCP | Self-hosted |\\n\\n## Architecture contrast\\n\\n**Orion Belt:** `Operator \u2192 Gateway \u2190 (reverse SSH) \u2190 Agent on target`\\n\\nThe target initiates the tunnel. The gateway brokers policy, recording, and live watch.\\n\\n**Traditional bastion:** still often means keys, little recording/JIT, and inbound exposure somewhere on the path.\\n\\n**Teleport-shaped platforms:** powerful and broad \u2014 correspondingly more to deploy and operate.\\n\\n## When to choose Orion Belt\\n\\n- Privileged access is **mostly SSH**\\n- You want **no inbound SSH** on app hosts\\n- You want **recording + live watch + JIT** without a PAM appliance\\n- You prefer **self-hosted**, Linux-first, inspectable code\\n- You\u2019re OK with a **narrower scope** today (OIDC/HA and more protocols are on the roadmap)\\n\\n## When Teleport (or similar) fits better\\n\\n- You need first-class **K8s / DB / Windows / web** access in one product now\\n- You\u2019re already standardized on that platform org-wide\\n\\n## Security tradeoff (reverse agents)\\n\\n**Gain:** targets need outbound reachability to the gateway, not inbound SSH.  \\n**Cost:** offline agents aren\u2019t reachable; the gateway is a high-value control plane \u2014 harden it.\\n\\n## Try before you debate\\n\\n[Try Orion Belt in 10 minutes](/docs/quickstart/try-in-10-minutes) \xb7 [GitHub](https://github.com/orion-belt-dev/orion-belt) \xb7 [Discord](https://discord.gg/w62S8jxTHJ)"},{"id":"welcome-orion-belt-v1","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/welcome-orion-belt-v1","editUrl":"https://github.com/zrougamed/orion-belt-docs/edit/master/blog/2026-07-16-welcome-orion-belt-v1.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-07-16-welcome-orion-belt-v1.md","title":"Orion Belt v1.0 is out","description":"Orion Belt v1.0 is a self-hosted SSH access gateway with PAM workflows: reverse agents, session recording, live watch, JIT approvals, MFA/WebAuthn, ReBAC, and optional SSH CA.","date":"2026-07-16T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"SSH","permalink":"/blog/tags/ssh","description":"SSH access, bastions, and tunnels"},{"inline":false,"label":"PAM","permalink":"/blog/tags/pam","description":"Privileged access management"},{"inline":false,"label":"Self-hosted","permalink":"/blog/tags/self-hosted","description":"Running infrastructure yourself"}],"readingTime":0.65,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Orion Belt","title":"Maintainers","url":"https://orion-belt.dev","page":{"permalink":"/blog/authors/orion"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/orion-belt-dev"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/orion-belt-dev.png","key":"orion"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"welcome-orion-belt-v1","title":"Orion Belt v1.0 is out","authors":["orion"],"tags":["ssh","pam","self-hosted"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Orion Belt vs Teleport (and Boundary / bastions)","permalink":"/blog/orion-belt-vs-teleport"}},"content":"**Orion Belt v1.0** is a self-hosted SSH access gateway with PAM workflows: reverse agents, session recording, live watch, JIT approvals, MFA/WebAuthn, ReBAC, and optional SSH CA.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n### Positioning\\n\\nTeleport-like SSH access control \u2014 without opening inbound ports on every host or adopting a large platform.\\n\\n### Try it\\n\\nAbout ten minutes to a recorded session:\\n\\n[Try Orion Belt in 10 minutes](/docs/quickstart/try-in-10-minutes)\\n\\n```bash\\ngit clone https://github.com/orion-belt-dev/orion-belt.git\\ncd orion-belt\\n./scripts/docker-quickstart.sh\\n```\\n\\n### License\\n\\nApache 2.0 + Commons Clause \u2014 free to self-host and use internally; you cannot sell Orion Belt as a product or hosted service.\\n\\n### Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/w62S8jxTHJ)\\n- [GitHub](https://github.com/orion-belt-dev/orion-belt)\\n- Looking for early operators \u2014 join Discord or open a Discussion"}]}}')}}]);